quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  38,27,"And We did not create the sky and the earth and whatever is between them without purpose. That is the thinking of those who disbelieve. So woe to those who disbelieved, from the fire"
  38,28,"Or should We place those who believed and did good works same as the corruptors on the earth, or should We place those who control themselves same as the immoral ones"
  38,29,"(This is) a blessed book that We sent it down to you, so that they think about its verses, and so that the people of understanding (reasonable people) take notice"
  38,30,"And We gave David Solomon, the good servant, indeed he was repentant"
  38,31,When he was presented with the stallions of excellent bread in the evening
  38,32,"Then he said: indeed I liked love of the good thing over remembrance of my Master, until they disappeared behind the curtain"
  38,33,"(He said) bring them back to me, and he rubbed the legs and the necks (of the horses)"
  38,34,"And We certainly tested Solomon by throwing a (dead) body on his chair, then he repented"
  38,35,"He said: my Master, forgive me, and give me a kingdom that is not likely for anyone after me, indeed you are the giver"
  38,36,Then We brought the wind under his control to blow gently by his command wherever he wanted
  38,37,"and the devils, all builder and diver"
  38,38,"and others, tied together"
  38,39,"(We told him): this is Our gift, so give or keep without any limit"
  38,40,And indeed he has closeness with Us and a good place of return
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he called his Master: indeed Satan touched me with pain and suffering"
  38,42,"(We told him:) stomp with your foot, this is cool water to wash and to drink"